Perl5.18 has some limited support for Perl6-style function signatures, but it&#x27;s still considered &quot;experimental&quot; and requires a pragma to enable. I don&#x27;t consider that to really be part of the language yet; real-world Perl5 function definitions end up looking like this, at best:<p><pre><code>    sub foo {
        my ($foo, @bar) = @_;
        ...
    }
</code></pre>
I&#x27;m not sure if that&#x27;s valid syntax in Perl6 or not, but either way it&#x27;s <i>certainly</i> not idiomatic.
